jobs_results.description:
Mandatory Skill-set
• Degree in Information Systems or related field;
• At least 5 years of hands-on support experience for fiduciary system or web based financial system;
• Experience with programming languages such as Java or .Net;
• Has experience supporting regional systems and stakeholders in maintaining system upgrades/ enhancements;
• Familiar with incident management, problem management, release management, root cause analysis and monitoring;
• Ability to work efficiently under pressure and meet tight deadlines;
• Good written and verbal communication skills.
Desired Skill-set
• Prior working experience in the financial industry.
Responsibilities
• Manage the enhancements and implementations of internal fiduciary and wealth systems;
• Provides L2 support to end-users for IT applications, not limited to web technologies (e.g. Java, .Net) as well as client-server applications;
• Work with Service Desk, Infrastructure support, database administrator, applications development... teams to identify and correct core issues;
• Identify and resolve problems from both incidents and BAUs;
• Perform user acceptance testing for successful system implementation and support related activities across IT teams;
• Provide insights to continuous improvements & innovation to increase productivity;
• Provide reports on defects and other status report for tracking /resolution purposes.
• Ensure adherence to the best practices of the development processes
